// Gap 2.4 repro in circuit mode — Movimiento 2 Phase 3G.
//
// Standalone `circuit Foo(...)` declaration that imports b.ach
// and calls b::middle() from inside the circuit body. middle's
// body references a module-private `helper()` as a bare
// identifier — that's what makes this a gap 2.4 scenario.
//
// Pre-Phase-3G this path is *worse* than the prove-block case:
// compile_circuit's legacy `register_module_exports` path only
// registers `b::middle` (exported) in the fn_table, NOT
// `b::helper` (private). When middle is inlined, its body's
// `helper()` lookup misses with UndeclaredVariable.
//
// Phase 3G fix: auto-build resolver state, walk the full graph,
// and pre-populate fn_table with both exported AND private fns
// under their correct alias-form keys.

import "./b.ach" as b

circuit Foo(expected: Public) {
    assert_eq(expected, b::middle())
}
